main event: One object was observed over Casselberry, Florida on 14 May 1966 for approximately one hour.
interesting points: The observation lasted for one hour and was conducted by a civilian., The object was reported to be moving in a westerly direction., There were no photographs or physical evidence collected during the observation., The Air Force deemed the data insufficient for evaluation., A diagram was included showing the location and movement of the observed object.
sighted object: one unidentified object in the sky
